Natural Period Estimates

DOFT_n (s)f_n (Hz)omega_n (rad/s)
SurgeDepends on mooring stiffness
SwayDepends on mooring stiffness
Heave2.0270.49343.1000
Roll4.1890.23871.5000

YawDepends on mooring stiffness

T_n = 2pi * sqrt((M_ii + A_ii(omega_n)) / C_ii). Surge, Sway, and Yaw natural periods depend on mooring stiffness (not available in diffraction analysis). These natural periods should correspond to RAO peak locations. Discrepancy > 5% warrants investigation.

Added Mass A(omega) -- Diagonal Terms

Added mass represents entrained water inertia. Generally increases at low frequencies. Dashed red lines mark natural periods from Section 6.

Radiation Damping B(omega) -- Diagonal Terms

Radiation damping represents energy lost to radiated waves. Peaks near natural frequency. Zero at omega=0 and omega->infinity.

Coupling Assessment

Off-diagonal coefficients with max |A_ij| / max(|A_ii|, |A_jj|) > 5% at any frequency. Significant coupling affects motion predictions and should be considered in design.

Phase Interpretation Guide

  • Phase = 0 deg: Response in-phase with wave (crest at origin = peak response)
  • Phase = -90 deg: Lagging (response peaks after wave crest passes)
  • Phase = +90 deg: Leading (response peaks before wave crest arrives)
  • ~180 deg jump near resonance: Transition from quasi-static to resonant regime
  • Phase at near-zero amplitude: Physically meaningless -- ignore phase when amplitude is insignificant

Appendices

A. Notation & Conventions

SymbolDescription
DOF 1-6Surge, Sway, Heave, Roll, Pitch, Yaw
Coordinate Systemx-forward, z-up, right-hand rule
A_ii(omega)Frequency-dependent added mass (diagonal)
B_ii(omega)Frequency-dependent radiation damping (diagonal)
C_iiHydrostatic restoring stiffness (diagonal)
GM_TTransverse metacentric height (metres)
T_nNatural period (seconds)
zetaCritical damping ratio (%)
RAOResponse Amplitude Operator

B. Key Formulas

  • T_n = 2pi * sqrt((M_ii + A_ii(omega_n)) / C_ii)
  • zeta(omega) = B_ii(omega) / (2 * sqrt((M_ii + A_ii(omega)) * C_ii))
  • GM_T = C_44 / (rho * g * V), where rho=1025 kg/m3, g=9.81 m/s2
  • BM_T = I_xx / V; GM_T = KB + BM_T - KG (cross-check)
